    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Millinery tools consisting of cast-iron, egg-shaped balls of various sizes mounted on metal shanks and fixed to a short wooden handle. Used to iron the inside of convex surfaces on bonnets, sleeves, bows, or waistbands.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
